\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 To create a weapon you must determine the following specific information about your particular weapon. The means by which you create a weapon also applies to the definition of the hand of a monster.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs36\lang2057 3.1\tab}\pard\plain \s2\qj\sb360\sa120\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl2\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 }\f4\fs36\lang2057 Weapon Category
\par \pard\plain \keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 Select a weapon type from the file {\i values.h}
 (one of the WPN_XXX macros which is larger than (after) WPN_GROUP_MAX). For example WPN_DAGGER. The weapon category determines which skill is required for using  (and defending against) the weapon.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs36\lang2057 3.2\tab}\pard\plain \s2\qj\sb360\sa120\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl2\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 }\f4\fs36\lang2057 Examples
\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 A standard macro \ldblquote WEAPON_DEF(weapon_category, craftsmanship, magic_bonus)\rdblquote  is available, and should be used for defining the weapons values.
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn Note that both craftsmanship & magic bonuses are in the range [-25%..+25%].
\par 
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn A flail (two handed) of non-pure iron (-3%), a little better than average craftsmanship (5%) and no magic bonuses would have:
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn \tab WEAPON_DEF(WPN_FLAIL, +2, 0)
\par 
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn A rusty (-5%) mean sacrificial dagger by a skilled smithy (+5%) and magically enchanted might be:
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn \tab flags \{UNIT_FL_MAGIC\}
\par \tab WEAPON_DEF(WPN_DAGGER, 0, +5)
\par 
\par An old shaky wooden stick could be:
\par \tab WEAPON_DEF(WPN_CLUB, -5, 0)
\par 
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn A wooden bastard sword would have considerable less craftsmanship than listed since wood prevents the \lquote slashing\rquote  effect, also it would be non-sense to apply better than average craftsmanship in this case:
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn \tab WEAPON_DEF(WPN_BROAD_SWORD, -15, 0)
\par 
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn Very special weapons ought to exist only in limited numbers even if they are not magical, for example, it seems unreasonable that hundreds of daggers made from diamond exists in the world. Perhaps only one or t
wo such weapons exist. Use the {\i max} field in the {\i load} or {\i equip} reset-commands.
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn 
