\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 This chapter describes the rules by which magical items must be created. The rules are made under the consideration that a player can equip a total of 17 items! It is therefore very important that you caref
ully follow these guidelines.
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn 
\par \pard \qc\keep\keepn {\b Magical bonuses are applied to a player\line whenever he equips a magical item.
\par }\pard \qj\keep\keepn 
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn When you create a magical item you should remember to set the unit-flag UNIT_FL_MAGIC so that the detect magic spell will work properly. But most of the used macros automatically set the magic flag. (flags \{
UNIT_FL_MAGIC\}).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs36\lang2057 7.1\tab}\pard\plain \s2\qj\sb360\sa120\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl2\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 }\f4\fs36\lang2057 Identifying Magical Items
\par \pard\plain \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 It is always important for the players to get information about magical items. The following method gives you the possibility of creating textual identification descriptions for the \ldblquote 
identify\rdblquote  and \ldblquote improved identify\rdblquote  spells.
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn Add an extra description with the keyword \ldblquote $identify\rdblquote  and it will show the description when an identify spell is cast upon the item.
\par Add an extra description with the keyword \ldblquote $improved identify\rdblquote  and it will show the description when an improved identify spell is cast upon the item.
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn Example: 
\par 
\par \tab crown_of_king
\par bla bla......
\par 
\par extra \{\ldblquote $identify\rdblquote \}
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn \ldblquote This once used to be the crown of the evil lich king Asmodeus, the greatest of the undead. The c
rown is a great magical item rumored to give its posessor fantastic intellectual powers. The crown can only be used by evil persons.\rdblquote 
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn 
\par extra \{\ldblquote $improved identify\rdblquote \}
\par \ldblquote The Crown of Asmodeus gives +5 to brain. Can only be used by evil persons.\rdblquote 
\par end
\par 
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn 
As you can see, the two types of descriptions associated with the magical items gives a lot more flavor to your magical items. Please always include both descriptions on any magical items you create (they can be used on any kind of item, even unmagical on
es, but {\i most likely }there is nothing special to be said about non-magical items).
\par \pard \qj\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn 
