\par \pard \s28\qj\sl240\slmult0\keep\keepn 
Illustrates how powerful a magical boost in ability is considered. If a boost is for example +2 to STR, it is considered 'powerful magic'. If a boost is to more than one ability, the bonuses are added, such that a +2 STR, +1 DEX is considered 'Demi-God Ma
gic'. If a boost is negative (a penalty) one additional bonus (positive) may be added for every -5 points of penalty to a maximum of +7 total. For example  +2 STR, +2 DEX, +3 CON, -10 BRA is allowed. In general, artifacts mean tha
t a maximum one such item exists in the world, and a Quest is needed to retrieve it.
\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn A magical ability boost is created on an item by using the XXX_TRANSFER({\i n}) macro from the file {\i wmacros.h}.
\par \pard \qj\keep\keepn 
\par The value {\i n} is restricted by the above guidelines and the following additional rules:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs26\lang2057 \'b7\tab}\pard \qj\fi-283\li283\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent283\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}Under no circumstances may the sum of the boost exceed +7 regardless of the penalties.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs26\lang2057 \'b7\tab}If an item boosts more than one ability, the sum of 'n' must still be maximum five!\line Example: BRA_TRANSFER(2), MAG_TRANSFER(3) (Power = Artifact).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs26\lang2057 \'b7\tab}If an item penalises, and the penalty is reasonable, an additional point of boosting is allowed for every five points of penalty.
