\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs36\lang2057 7.6\tab}\pard\plain \s2\qj\sb360\sa120\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl2\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 }\f4\fs36\lang2057 Weapons of Slaying
\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 It is possible to create weapons that are designed to
 slay a particular race of monsters. Weapons slaying particular races have count as one-two points of ability in the table above, depending on the race. A goblin slayer would only count as one, whereas a human slayer would definitely count as two.
\par Use the macro \ldblquote WEAPON_SLAYER(race)\rdblquote  where race is one of the RACE_XXX in the values.h file.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs30\lang2057 7.6.1\tab}\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl3\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 {\pntxtb .}}\f4\fs30\lang2057 Example
\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 \tab WEAPON_SLAYER(RACE_GOBLIN)
\par 
\par Use a price multiplier of 2.0.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs36\lang2057 7.7\tab}\pard\plain \s2\qj\sb360\sa120\sl360\slmult0\keep\keepn{\*\pn \pnlvl2\pndec\pnprev1\pnstart1\pnsp144 }\f4\fs36\lang2057 Boosting skills
\par \pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn \f4\fs26\lang2057 By boosting skills you can enhance a characters skills, spells or weapon abilities. For example, in the file values.h SKI_FLEE is a skill, SPL_FIREBALL_3 is the \lquote fireball\rquote 
 spell and WPN_DAGGER is a weapon ability.
\par The rules for boosting are exactly the same as for abilities, except that all boosts / penalties have double range. {\field{\*\fldinst  REF _Ref289706882 \\* MERGEFORMAT }{\fldrslt Table }}
 shows the allowed range of skill boosts. Remember to use the price multipliers above for each spell in the item.
